{
  "page": "Kin of the Stag",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><i><b>Kin of the Stag</b></i> is a work by Maester <a href=\"/index.php/Hubert\" title=\"Hubert\">Hubert</a>, who suggests that <a href=\"/index.php/Galladon_of_Morne\" title=\"Galladon of Morne\">Galladon of Morne</a> was a historic figure of more recent times, and not some rude warrior from the <a href=\"/index.php/Age_of_Heroes\" title=\"Age of Heroes\">Age of Heroes</a>. The book also describes that, while <a href=\"/index.php/Morne\" title=\"Morne\">Morne</a> was the seat of petty kings on the eastern shores of <a href=\"/index.php/Tarth\" title=\"Tarth\">Tarth</a> until the <a href=\"/index.php/Storm_King\" title=\"Storm King\">Storm Kings</a> forced them to submit, Morne's ruins seem to indicate it was made by <a href=\"/index.php/Andals\" title=\"Andals\">Andals</a> and not <a href=\"/index.php/First_Men\" title=\"First Men\">First Men</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiaf_the_men_of_the_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiaf_the_men_of_the_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Kin_of_the_Stag&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiaf_the_men_of_the_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiaf_the_men_of_the_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp;